KATSE DAM - Parts of South Africa are experiencing water rationing as the drought continues. The Katse Dam is an absolute engineering marvel and forms part of the greater Lesotho Highlands Water Project. It provides Gauteng with 40 percent of its water. WATCH: Drought and water scarcity crisis to be resolved? But, is this project enough to allay Gauteng’s water woes? eNCA reporter Michael Appel travelled to the source of much of South Africa’s water in the Lesotho Mountains for a first-hand experience of the situation. Click the video above to view his report from Lesotho. eNCA